<span id="freeTextContainer9837965637027418287">This one offers an interesting take. The entire Mahabharata is narrated by Bhima. It is curious how the author has interpreted the feelings of Bhima as he is shown to live in the shadows of Arjuna. I also like it that the character is shown to be unburdened by thinking and lives an almost instinctive life. It is also interesting how the author weaves in narratives around lesser known characters like Hidimbi. Top notch book for me!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


