<div id="review_1923074713" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1923074713" />
    <a title="Naveen Vijay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/46292616-naveen-vijay"><img alt="Naveen Vijay" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1440495524p2/46292616.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1923074713?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Naveen Vijay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Naveen Vijay" href="/user/show/46292616-naveen-vijay">Naveen Vijay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1923074713" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3319996781046896651">It was an excellent read. Being an avid reader and fan of Mahabharata, the world inside it always fonded me. The original Mahabharata, being written as an incident and not in anybody&apos;s perspective, always craved me to think about how the world that time would look like. This was the first thing that really attracted me to this book. The grand scale of the palaces can be easily envisioned and be mesmerized. <br/>How M.T have deliberately left out the element of fantasy is quiet fascinating; keeping th</span>
  <span id="freeText3319996781046896651" style="display:none">It was an excellent read. Being an avid reader and fan of Mahabharata, the world inside it always fonded me. The original Mahabharata, being written as an incident and not in anybody's perspective, always craved me to think about how the world that time would look like. This was the first thing that really attracted me to this book. The grand scale of the palaces can be easily envisioned and be mesmerized. <br />How M.T have deliberately left out the element of fantasy is quiet fascinating; keeping the story down to earth rather than lifting it high. The clever one liners and interesting "M.T twist" are nothing short of magnificence. <br />IN ONE WORD , YOU ARE WATCHING A HIGH BUDGET ACTION MOVIE, WITH A LOT OF EMOTIONAL CONTENT.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3319996781046896651" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


