        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2334822662?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kavitha Sivakumar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kavitha Sivakumar" href="/user/show/2206767-kavitha-sivakumar">Kavitha Sivakumar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789350297599" href="/book/show/18481907-bhima-lone-warrior">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2206767-kavitha-sivakumar?shelf=ir-india-2018">ir-india-2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2334822662" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8994485257082992401">A rendition of Mahabaratha that humanizes almost everything including that the pandavas are not born because of the boons but because of illicit affairs of Kundi. To be honest, the author says it convincingly. <br/><br/>Otherwise, the story doesn&apos;t catch my attention. Even when the story is told from Bhima&apos;s point of view, the story didn&apos;t change. Yudishtra, Draupadi and Krishna are portrayed in a very negative manner.<br/><br/>A disappointment.</span>
  <span id="freeText8994485257082992401" style="display:none">A rendition of Mahabaratha that humanizes almost everything including that the pandavas are not born because of the boons but because of illicit affairs of Kundi. To be honest, the author says it convincingly. <br /><br />Otherwise, the story doesn't catch my attention. Even when the story is told from Bhima's point of view, the story didn't change. Yudishtra, Draupadi and Krishna are portrayed in a very negative manner.<br /><br />A disappointment.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8994485257082992401" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


